while doing my paper, ive read a lot of quotes by franz kafka, which i find to be profound and meaningful and deep.  heres some of them that i think you might enjoy, ;)!!!

"Youth is happy because it has the ability to 
see beauty. Anyone who keeps the ability 
to see beauty never grows old."

"...the innocent and the guilty, both 
executed without distinction in the 
end.... "

My peers, lately, have found companionship through means of intoxication--it makes 
them sociable. I, however, cannot force 
myself to use drugs to cheat on my 
loneliness--it is all that I have--and 
when the drugs and alcohol dissipate, 
will be all that my peers have as well. 

"In the fight between you and the world, back the world."

	
"The tremendous world I have inside my head. 
But how free myself and free it without being 
torn to pieces. And a thousand times rather be 
torn to pieces than retain it in me or bury it. 
That, indeed, is why I am here, that is quite 
clear to me."

"Wisdom is thus not what men first of all seek 
They seek, instead, the justification for what 
they happen to cherish."

"It is the thousandth forgetting of a dream dreamt a thousand times
and forgotten a thousand times, and who can damn us merely for 
forgetting for the thousandth time?"

"a belief is like a guillotine, just as heavy, just as light."

"If I felt in love, I would be in a world
in which I could not live."

today mr Ricky Williams, former RB for the miami dolphins, filed papers for retirement after only 5 years in the NFL.  this annoucement came after he received news that he had failed his 3rd drug test.  and by signing the retirement papers, he is no longer to drug testing by the NFL.  mr clarkson told the newspaper his desire to continue smoking marijuana played a role in his decision to retire after 5 pro seasons.
